parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt can cause the belt to not engage or retract properly, leading to a lack of protection for the driver and passengers in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt does not engage or retract properly
the belt comes undone while driving
the belt does not slide on the rail properly
the motorized shoulder belt fails to retract
the belt releases and comes forward when going over a bump
the belt does not engage when the vehicle is started
the belt is stuck in the up position
the belt does not retract on the driver's side.
